                <p xml:id="KR3i0011-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-44a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-12-05T22:35:24.897+09:00">"beginning" plumbs with the unchanging (mode of shi) CH</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-73a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T09:59:05.599+09:00">As the theoretical point of logic, oxen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-73a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T09:53:15.441+09:00">demarcated from non-oxen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-73a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T09:53:44.836+09:00">constitute the dyad.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-73a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:11:00.715+09:00">When there is no basis (for determining oxhood of something) this means it is not an ox.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-133a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:17:07.132+09:00">As a general theoretical point of principle, regarding any object that weighs,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-133a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:18:53.354+09:00">if from above one will not pull it</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-133a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:19:52.229+09:00">from below one will not receive&gt;support it,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-133a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:20:15.505+09:00">and from the sides one does not push it</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-133a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:21:11.005+09:00">then its movement downwards will be straight.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-236a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:29:25.974+09:00">Speaking theoretially of the trying to learn love of others</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-236a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:31:28.953+09:00">when in their benefit to All under the Sun these others are equal to each other</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-236a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T10:33:47.877+09:00">then one should prefer any to any other.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-254a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T11:12:40.455+09:00">Johnston: 類在巾几  the analogy lies in the towel and thetable.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-254a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-22T11:09:23.718+09:00">Johnston: Small benevolence and great benevolence — in action their“weight” is the same;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3i0011_tls_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-24T19:45:45.489+09:00">this is still incomprehensible</seg>
                </p>
